2, '''81'''\u201313, 38\u201377, 31\u201378, '''69'''\u201340, '''79'''\u201336, 31\u201371, '''52'''\u201337, 14\u2013115, 61\u201370, '''84'''\u201349, '''69'''\u201336, '''60'''\u201358, 0\u201379, 9\u2013112, 0\u2013139\n|Century breaks: 2 (Higgins 2)<br/>\nHighest break by Reardon: 95<br/>\nHighest break by Higgins: 135\n|41\u2013'''61''', 64\u201331, 84\u201347, 0\u2013'''121''', 64\u201353, 77\u201330, 65\u201355, 28\u2013'''87''', 8\u2013'''89''', 76\u20138, 47\u2013'''56''', 22\u2013'''91''', 69\u201329, 4\u2013'''96''', 36\u2013'''71''', 14\u2013'''94''', 13\u2013'''73''', 122\u201312, 81\u201313, 38\u2013'''77''', 31\u2013'''78''', 69\u201340, 79\u201336, 31\u2013'''71''', 52\u201337, 14\u2013'''115''', 61\u2013'''70''', 84\u201349, 69\u201336, 60\u201358, 0\u2013'''79''', 9\u2013'''112''', 0\u2013'''139'''\n|'''{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} Alex Higgins''' wins the 1982 Embassy World Snooker Championship\n<!--  Frame header info -->\n|Best of 19 frames\n|Best of 25 frames\n|Best of 25 frames\n|Best of 31 frames\n}}\n\n== Century breaks ==\nThere were 10 [[century break]]s at the championship, the highest being 143 by [[Willie Thorne]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kastner |first=Hugo |title=Snooker \u2013 Spieler, Regeln & Rekorde (May 2011 update) |url=http://www.hugo-kastner.at/snooker_crucible_records_mai11.pdf |accessdate=27 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/67yvQWyOm?url=http://www.hugo-kastner.at/snooker_crucible_records_mai11.pdf |archivedate=27 May 2012 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Crucible Centuries |url=http://www.snooker.org/Plr/wc_centuries.shtml |publisher=Snooker.org |accessdate=3 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110523045039/http://www.snooker.org/plr/wc_centuries.shtml |archivedate=23 May 2011  }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Downer|first=Chris|title=Crucible Almanac|year=2012|pages=146}}</ref> There was also a \u00a35,000 bonus on offer for compiling a higher break than the championship record of 145.<ref name=\"Almanac prize money\"/>\n* 143, 122, 112, 106 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Willie Thorne]]\n* 135, 118 {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Alex Higgins]]\n* 126, 102 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jimmy White]]\n* 111 {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Kirk Stevens]]\n* 100 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[John Virgo]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{World Snooker Championship}}\n{{Snooker season 1981/1982}}\n\n[[Category:World Snooker Championships|1982]]\n[[Category:1982 in snooker|World Championship]]\n[[Category:1982 in English sport|World Snooker Championship]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Sheffield]]\n[[Category:April 1982 sports events in the United Kingdom|World Snooker Championship]]\n[[Category:May 1982 sports events in the United Kingdom|World Snooker Championship]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2013}}\n{{Infobox individual snooker tournament\n|tournament_name=[[Embassy (cigarette)|Embassy]] [[World Snooker Championship]]\n|logo=\n|dates=30 April\u201316 May 1982\n|venue=[[Crucible Theatre]]\n|location=Sheffield\n|country=England\n|organisation=[[World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association|WPBSA]]\n|format=[[Snooker world rankings|Ranking]] event\n|Total prize fund=[[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]110,000\n|winners_share=\u00a325,000\n|highest_break={{flagicon|ENG}} [[Willie Thorne]] (143)\n|winner={{flagicon|NIR}} [[Alex Higgins]]\n|runner_up={{flagicon|WAL}} [[Ray Reardon]]\n|score=18\u201315\n|previous=[[1981 World Snooker Championship|1981]]\n|next=[[1983 World Snooker Championship|1983]]}}\n\nThe '''1982 World Snooker Championship''' (also known as the '''1982 Embassy World Snooker Championship''' for sponsorship purposes) was a professional [[Snooker world rankings|ranking]] [[snooker]] tournament that took place between 30 April and 16 May 1982 at the [[Crucible Theatre]] in [[Sheffield]], England.\n\n[[Alex Higgins]] won his second world title, defeating [[Ray Reardon]] 18\u201315 in the final.  The tournament was sponsored by cigarette manufacturer [[Embassy (cigarette)|Embassy]].\n\n== Tournament summary ==\n* The previous three world champions, who were also the top three seeds, were all defeated in the first round: defending champion [[Steve Davis]] lost 1\u201310 to [[Tony Knowles (snooker player)|Tony Knowles]], [[1979 World Snooker Championship|1979]] champion [[Terry Griffiths]] lost 6\u201310 to [[Willie Thorne]] and world number 1 and [[1980 World Snooker Championship|1980]] champion [[Cliff Thorburn]] lost 4\u201310 to [[Jimmy White]].<ref name=\"Global Snooker\"/>\n* Higgins reached the final after an epic 16\u201315 semi-final victory over Jimmy White. Trailing 15\u201314 and 59\u20130, Higgins saved himself with a memorable clearance of 69 and then won the decider for a place in the final.<ref>[http://www1.skysports.com/snooker/news/12040/6278243/davis-leads-higgins-tributes Davis leads Higgins tributes]</ref> The final between Higgins and Reardon was a repeat of the [[1976 World Snooker Championship|1976 final]], which Reardon won 27\u201316. From 15\u201315, Higgins won the next three frames and clinched the title with a break of 135 in the final frame. A tearful Higgins summoned his wife and baby daughter from the audience to celebrate with him.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/in_depth/2001/world_snooker_championship/1244064.stm Crucible's top 10 moments]</ref>\n* [[Jim Donnelly (snooker player)|Jim Donnelly]] became the first [[Scottish people|Scottish]] player to play at the Crucible. He lost in the first round 5\u201310 to [[Ray Reardon]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Hendon|first=David|title=The Thursday Quiz (Answers)|url=http://snookerscene.blogspot.com/2010/10/thursday-quiz-answers_22.html|publisher=Snooker Scene Blog|accessdate=3 April 2012}}</ref>\n* This was the first tournament in which the top 8 seeds had to play in the first round, taking the tournament from 24 to 32 players. This format still remains today.<ref name=\"Snooker Scene WSC\">{{cite web|title=Embassy World Championship |url=http://www.snookerscene.co.uk/page.php?id=36 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130124071753/http://www.snookerscene.co.uk/page.php?id=36 |archivedate=24 January 2013 |publisher=Snooker Scene |accessdate=3 April 2012 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\n==Prize fund==\nThe breakdown of prize money for this year is shown below:<ref name=\"Almanac prize money\">{{cite book|last=Downer|first=Chris|title=Crucible Almanac|year=2012|pages=130}}</ref> \n* Winner: \u00a325,000\n* Runner-up: \u00a312,500\n* Semi-final: \u00a37,000\n* Quarter-final: \u00a33,500\n* Last 16: \u00a32,250\n* Last 32: \u00a31,250\n* Highest break: \u00a32,500\n* [[Maximum break]]: \u00a310,000\n* Total: \u00a3110,000\n\n== Main draw ==\nShown below are the results for each round. The numbers in parentheses beside some of the players are their seeding ranks (each championship has 16 seeds and 16 qualifiers).<ref name=\"Global Snooker\">{{cite web|title=World Championship 1982|url=http://www.global-snooker.com/professional-snooker-tournaments-archive-world-championship-1982.asp|publisher=Global Snooker|accessdate=3 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306014346/http://www.global-snooker.com/professional-snooker-tournaments-archive-world-championship-1982.asp|archive-date=6 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Snooker Scene WSC\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=1982 World Championships Results|url=http://snookerdatabase.co.uk/EventResults.aspx?EventKey=30|publisher=Snooker Database|accessdate=3 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Downer|first=Chris|title=Crucible Almanac|year=2012|pages=4\u20135}}</ref>\n{{World Snooker Championship Rounds\n<!--Date-Place/Player 1/Score 1/Player 2/Score 2 -->\n<!-- LAST 32 -->\n<!--Match1  -->\n|30 April & 1 May|{{flagicon|England}} [[Steve Davis]] (1)|1|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Tony Knowles (snooker player)|Tony Knowles]]'''|'''10'''\n<!--Match2 -->\n|30 April & 1 May|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Graham Miles]] (16)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Dave Martin (snooker player)|Dave Martin]]|5\n<!--Match3  -->\n|1 & 2 May|{{flagicon|Canada}} '''[[Bill Werbeniuk]] (9)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|Canada}} [[John Bear (snooker player)|John Bear]]|7\n<!--Match4  -->\n|1 & 2 May|{{flagicon|Australia}} '''[[Eddie Charlton]] (8)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|Wales}} [[Cliff Wilson]]|5\n<!--Match5  -->\n|1 & 2 May|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} [[Dennis Taylor]] (5)|7|{{flagicon|South Africa|1928}} '''[[Silvino Francisco]]'''|'''10'''\n<!--Match6  -->\n|1 & 2 May|{{flagicon|England}} [[Fred Davis (snooker player)|Fred Davis]] (12)|7|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Dean Reynolds]]'''|'''10'''\n<!--Match7  -->\n|2 & 3 May|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[John Virgo]] (13)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Mike Hallett]]|4\n<!--Match8  -->\n|2 & 3 May|{{flagicon|Wales}} '''[[Ray Reardon]] (4)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Jim Donnelly (snooker player)|Jim Donnelly]]|5\n<!--Match9 -->\n|3 & 4 May|{{flagicon|Wales}} [[Terry Griffiths]] (3)|6|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Willie Thorne]]'''|'''10'''\n<!--Match10  -->\n|3 & 4 May|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[John Spencer (snooker player)|John Spencer]] (14)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[John Dunning (snooker player)|John Dunning]]|4\n<!--Match11  -->\n|3 & 4 May|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} '''[[Alex Higgins]] (11)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Jim Meadowcroft]]|5\n<!--Match12  -->\n|3 & 4 May|{{flagicon|Wales}} '''[[Doug Mountjoy]] (6)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Rex Williams]]|3\n<!--Match13  -->\n|4 & 5 May|{{flagicon|England}} [[David Taylor (snooker player)|David Taylor]] (7)|9|{{flagicon|Ireland}} '''[[Patsy Fagan]]'''|'''10'''\n<!--Match14  -->\n|4 & 5 May|{{flagicon|Canada}} '''[[Kirk Stevens]] (10)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Jack Fitzmaurice]]|4\n<!--Match15  -->\n|5 & 6 May|{{flagicon|South Africa|1928}} '''[[Perrie Mans]] (15)'''|'''10'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Tony Meo]]|8\n<!--Match16  -->\n|5 & 6 May|{{flagicon|Canada}} [[Cliff Thorburn]] (2)|4|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Jimmy White]]'''|'''10'''\n<!-- Last 16 -->\n<!--Match1  -->\n|5 & 6 May|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Tony Knowles (snooker player)|Tony Knowles]]'''|'''13'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Graham Miles]] (16)|7\n<!--Match2  -->\n|5, 6 & 7 May|{{flagicon|Canada}} [[Bill Werbeniuk]] (9)|5|{{flagicon|Australia}} '''[[Eddie Charlton]] (8)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match3  -->\n|7 & 8 May|{{flagicon|South Africa|1928}} '''[[Silvino Francisco]]'''|'''13'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[Dean Reynolds]]|8\n<!--Match4  -->\n|6, 7 & 8 May|{{flagicon|England}} [[John Virgo]] (13)|8|{{flagicon|Wales}} '''[[Ray Reardon]] (4)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match5  -->\n|7 & 8 May|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Willie Thorne]]'''|'''13'''|{{flagicon|England}} [[John Spencer (snooker player)|John Spencer]] (14)|5\n<!--Match6  -->\n|7, 8 & 9 May|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} '''[[Alex Higgins]] (11)'''|'''13'''|{{flagicon|Wales}} [[Doug Mountjoy]] (6)|12\n<!--Match7  -->\n|9 & 10 May|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Patsy Fagan]]|7|{{flagicon|Canada}} '''[[Kirk Stevens]] (10)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match8  -->\n|8 & 9 May|{{flagicon|South Africa|1928}} [[Perrie Mans]] (15)|6|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Jimmy White]]'''|'''13'''\n<!-- QUARTER-FINALS -->\n<!--Match1  -->\n|9, 10 & 11 May|{{flagicon|England}} [[Tony Knowles (snooker player)|Tony Knowles]]|11|{{flagicon|Australia}} '''[[Eddie Charlton]] (8)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match2  -->\n|10 & 11 May|{{flagicon|South Africa|1928}} [[Silvino Francisco]]|8|{{flagicon|Wales}} '''[[Ray Reardon]] (4)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match3  -->\n|10 & 11 May|{{flagicon|England}} [[Willie Thorne]]|10|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}} '''[[Alex Higgins]] (11)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match4  -->\n|10 & 11 May|{{flagicon|Canada}} [[Kirk Stevens]] (10)|9|{{flagicon|England}} '''[[Jimmy White]]'''|'''13'''\n<!-- SEMI-FINALS -->\n<!--Match1  -->\n|12, 13 & 14 May|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Eddie Charlton]] (8)|11|{{flagicon|Wales}} '''[[Ray Reardon]] (4)'''|'''16'''\n<!--Match2  -->\n|