''[[Christmas Memories]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[The Movie Album (Barbra Streisand album)|The Movie Album]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2004 || rowspan=\"2\"|'''Grammy Hall of Fame''' || ''[[Funny Girl (musical)|Funny Girl]]'' <small>(Barbra Streisand and [[Sydney Chaplin (American actor)|Sydney Chaplin]])</small> || rowspan=\"2\" align=center| '''Inducted'''\n|-\n| 2006 ||  ''[[The Barbra Streisand Album]]''\n|-\n| 2007 || Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album || ''[[Live in Concert 2006]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008 || '''Grammy Hall of Fame''' || \"[[The Way We Were (song)|The Way We Were]]\" || align=center| '''Inducted'''\n|-\n| 2011 || Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album || ''[[Love Is the Answer (album)|Love Is the Answer]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2012 || Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album || ''[[What Matters Most]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2015 || Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album || ''[[Partners (Barbra Streisand album)|Partners]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2017 || Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album || ''[[Encore: Movie Partners Sing Broadway]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2020 || Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album || ''[[Walls (Barbra Streisand album)|Walls]]'' || {{nom}}\n|}\n\n=== Film awards ===\nStreisand has won two [[Academy Award]]s (Oscar) against five nominations: two for acting, two for songwriting and one for [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]. She won Oscars for Best Actress (''Funny Girl'') and Best Original Song (\"Evergreen\"). The three films she directed received a total of 14 Oscar nominations.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Work !! Result !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1969 || [[Academy Awards]] || Best Actress || rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Funny Girl (film)|Funny Girl]]'' || {{Won}} || Tied with [[Katharine Hepburn]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| [[Golden Globe Awards]] || rowspan=\"2\"|Best Actress in a Motion Picture (Comedy or Musical) || {{Won}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1970 || ''[[Hello, Dolly! (film)|Hello, Dolly!]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| [[Henrietta Award|Henrietta World Film Favorite]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"|\u2014 || '''Special award''' ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1971 || Best Actress in a Motion Picture (Comedy or Musical) || ''[[The Owl and the Pussycat (film)|The Owl and the Pussycat]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| Henrietta World Film Favorite || style=\"text-align:center;\"|\u2014 || '''Special award''' ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1974 || Academy Awards || Best Actress || rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[The Way We Were]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|Golden Globe Awards || Best Actress in a Motion Picture (Drama) || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| 1975 || Henrietta World Film Favorite || style=\"text-align:center;\"|\u2014 || '''Special award''' ||\n|-\n| 1976 || Best Actress in a Motion Picture (Comedy or Musical) || ''[[Funny Lady]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1977 || Academy Awards || Best Original Song || rowspan=\"3\"| \"[[Evergreen (Love Theme from A Star Is Born)|Evergreen]]\" <small>(from ''[[A Star Is Born (1976 film)|A Star Is Born]]'')</small> || {{Won}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"|Golden Globe Awards || Best Actress in a Motion Picture (Comedy or Musical)  || {{Won}} ||\n|-\n| Best Original Song || {{Won}} ||\n|-\n| 1978 || Henrietta World Film Favorite || style=\"text-align:center;\"|\u2014 || '''Special award''' ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1984 || Best Actress in a Motion Picture (Comedy or Musical) || rowspan=\"4\"| ''[[Yentl (film)|Yentl]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| Best Director (Motion Picture) || {{Won}} ||\n|-\n| Best Motion Picture (Comedy Or Musical) || {{Won}} ||\n|-\n| 1983 || [[Golden Raspberry Awards]] || [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Actor]] ||{{nom}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1988 || rowspan=\"2\"|Golden Globe Awards||Best Actress in Motion Picture (Drama) || rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Nuts (1987 film)|Nuts]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| Best Motion Picture (Drama) || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1992 || Academy Awards || Best Picture || rowspan=\"3\"| ''[[The Prince of Tides]]'' || {{nom}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\