lbum]] by American vocal group [[Wilson Phillips]], released in 1990. Five singles were released from the album, with \"[[Hold On (Wilson Phillips song)|Hold On]]\", \"[[Release Me (Wilson Phillips song)|Release Me]]\" and \"[[You're in Love (Wilson Phillips song)|You're in Love]]\" all hitting number one on the U.S. [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] singles chart. \"[[Impulsive (song)|Impulsive]]\" reached number four, and the fifth single \"The Dream Is Still Alive\" reached the top 20. The album has sold 5 million copies in the United States and over 10 million worldwide.\n\n==Track listing==\n;Side 1\n{{tracklist\n| title1          = [[Hold On (Wilson Phillips song)|Hold On]]\n| writer1         = [[Carnie Wilson]], [[Chynna Phillips]], [[Glen Ballard]]\n| length1         = 4:27\n| title2          = [[Release Me (Wilson Phillips song)|Release Me]]\n| writer2         = Wilson Phillips\n| length2         = 4:56\n| title3          = [[Impulsive (song)|Impulsive]]\n| writer3         = [[Steve Kipner]], [[Clif Magness]]\n| length3         = 4:34\n| title4          = Next to You (Someday I'll Be)\n| writer4         = [[Darrell Brown (musician)|Darrell Brown]], [[David Batteau]], [[Madeline Stone]]\n| length4         = 4:57\n| title5          = [[You're in Love (Wilson Phillips song)|You're in Love]]\n| writer5         = Wilson Phillips, Glen Ballard\n| length5         = 4:51\n}}\n\n;Side 2\n{{tracklist\n| title6          = Over and Over\n| writer6         = Wilson Phillips, Glen Ballard\n| length6         = 4:40\n| title7          = [[Reason to Believe|A Reason to Believe]]\n| writer7         = [[Tim Hardin]]\n| length7         = 4:04\n| title8          = Ooh You're Gold\n| writer8         = Wilson Phillips, Glen Ballard\n| length8         = 4:19\n| title9          = Eyes Like Twins\n| writer9         = [[Rupert Hine]], [[Jeanette Obstoj|Jeanette Therese Obstoj]]\n| length9         = 5:03\n| title10         = [[The Dream Is Still Alive]]\n| writer10        = 