Spain}}\n|{{flag|Spanish State}}\n|align=center| {{dts|February 18, 2015}}\n|align=center| present\n|}\n\n==By birthplace==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Country\n!State or Province\n!No. of governors\n|-\n|[[Austria]]\n|align=right|[[Styria]]\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Canada]]\n|align=right|[[Alberta]]\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|align=right|[[British Columbia]]\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|align=right|[[Colony of New Brunswick]]\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|align=right|[[Ontario]]\n|align=center| 4\n|-\n|align=right|[[Quebec]]\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|align=right|TOTAL\n|align=center| '''9'''\n|-\n|[[Cuba]]\n|align=right|[[Havana]]\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|[[Denmark]]\n|align=right|[[Zealand]]\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|[[Estonia]]\n|\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[France]]\n|align=right|[[Hauts-de-France]]\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|align=right|[[Paris]]\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|align=right|TOTAL\n|align=center| '''3'''\n|-\n|[[Germany]]\n|\n|align=center| '''7'''\n|-\n|[[Ireland]]\n|\n|align=center| '''4'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Mexico]]\n|align=right|[[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]]\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|align=right|[[Sonora]]\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|align=right|TOTAL\n|align=center| '''3'''\n|-\n|[[Norway]]\n|\n|align=center| '''5'''\n|-\n|[[Poland]]\n|align=right|[[Province of Posen]]\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|[[Spain]]\n|align=right|[[Community of Madrid]]\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|[[Sweden]]\n|\n|align=center| '''5'''\n|-\n|[[Switzerland]]\n|align=right|[[Canton of Z\u00fcrich]]\n|align=center| '''1'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[United Kingdom]]\n|align=right|[[England]]\n|align=center| 15\n|-\n|align=right|[[Northern Ireland]]\n|align=center| 6\n|-\n|align=right|[[Scotland]]\n|align=center| 7\n|-\n|align=right|[[Wales]]\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|align=right|TOTAL\n|align=center| '''29'''\n|}\n\n==By state==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!State\n!No. of governors\n|-\n|{{flag|Alabama}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Arizona}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|California}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|Connecticut}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|Delaware}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Georgia (U.S. state)|name=Georgia}}\n|align=center| 6\n|-\n|{{flag|Idaho}}\n|align=center| 3\n|-\n|{{flag|Illinois}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|Louisiana}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|Massachusetts}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|Michigan}}\n|align=center| 4\n|-\n|{{flag|Minnesota}}\n|align=center| 4\n|-\n|{{flag|Montana}}\n|align=center| 3\n|-\n|{{flag|Nebraska}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Nevada}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|New Hampshire}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|New Jersey}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|New Mexico}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|North Carolina}}\n|align=center| 3\n|-\n|{{flag|North Dakota}}\n|align=center| 4\n|-\n|{{flag|Ohio}}\n|align=center| 4\n|-\n|{{flag|Oregon}}\n|align=center| 4\n|-\n|{{flag|Pennsylvania}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Rhode Island}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|South Dakota}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Utah}}\n|align=center| 3\n|-\n|{{flag|Vermont}}\n|align=center| 2\n|-\n|{{flag|Virginia}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Washington}}\n|align=center| 1\n|-\n|{{flag|Wisconsin}}\n|align=center |5\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of United States senators born outside the United States]]\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of current United States governors]]\n* [[List of female governors in the United States]]\n* [[List of minority governors and lieutenant governors in the United States]]\n* [[Oldest living United States governor|List of oldest living United States governors]]\n* [[List of United States Senators born outside the United States]]\n\n{{US Chief Executives}}\n{{Current U.S. governors}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of state governors of the United States|State governors outside]]\n[[Category:American people by ethnic or national origin]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n\n[[File:Kate Brown in September 2015.jpg|thumb|right|[[Kate Brown]], [[Governor of Oregon]] since February 2015, was born in Spain, making her the only current U.S. governor who was born outside the United States.]]\n[[File:Arnold Schwarzenegger.jpg|thumb|right|[[Arnold Schwarzenegger]], [[Governor of California]] from 2003 to 2011, born in Austria, is the second most recent U.S. governor to have been born outside of the country.]]\n[[File:Jennifer Granholm (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|Canadian-born [[Jennifer Granholm]], [[Governor of Michigan]] from 2003 to 2011, is the third most recent U.S. governor to have been born outside the country.]]\n[[File:GovJohnSununu1.jpg|thumb|right|[[John H. Sununu]], [[Governor of New Hampshire]] from 1983 to 1989, was the first U.S. governor who was born in the [[Caribbean]].]]\n[[File:Octaviano_Larrazolo,_bw_photo_portrait,_1919.jpg|thumb|right|[[Octaviano Ambrosio Larrazolo]], [[Governor of New Mexico]] from 1919 to 1921, was the first U.S. governor who was born in [[Latin America]].]]\n[[File:Knute_Nelson_cph.3a45938.jpg|thumb|right|[[Knute Nelson]], [[Governor of Minnesota]] from 1893 to 1895, was the first U.S. governor who was born in [[Scandinavia]].]]\n[[File:Jacob_Dolson_Cox_Brady-Handy.jpg|thumb|right|[[Jacob Dolson Cox]], [[Governor of Ohio]] from 1866 to 1868, was the first U.S. governor who was born outside the United States, but still within the [[Americas]].]]\n[[File:John_Adam_Treutlen.jpg|thumb|right|[[John A. Treutlen]], [[Governor of Georgia]] from 1777 to 1778, was the first U.S. governor who was born in a non-[[English-speaking country]].]]\nIn total, 72 [[Governor (United States)|governors]] of a [[U.S. state]] have been born outside the current territory of the [[United States]]. [[Kate Brown]] of Oregon, born in Spain, is the only [[List of current United States governors|current governor]] to have been born outside the United States. [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] of California and [[Jennifer Granholm]] of Michigan (whose terms both ended in January 2011) are the other two most recent foreign-born governors.\n\nOf the fifty states, 30 (or 60 percent) have had at least one governor born outside the United States. 19 states have had multiple governors who were born outside the United States. [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] has had six foreign-born governors, who all served in office during the 18th century. The other states with the most foreign-born governors are [[Wisconsin]] (five), [[Michigan]], [[Minnesota]], [[North Dakota]], [[Ohio]], and [[Oregon]] (four each). Additionally, from 1905 to 1921 [[Utah]] had three consecutive foreign-born governors ([[John Christopher Cutler|John Cutler]], [[William Spry]], and [[Simon Bamberger]]).\n\nOf the 72 foreign-born governors, 59 were born in Europe and thirteen were born in North America, including the Caribbean. A total of 29 U.S. governors have been born on the present territory of the [[United Kingdom|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland]] (fifteen in England, seven in Scotland, six in Northern Ireland, and one in Wales), with another 2  born on territory of the Republic of Ireland while part of the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]], and 2 while part of the pre-union [[Kingdom of Ireland]]. Nine governors have been born within the present territory of Canada, seven Germany, five Norway, five Sweden, three France, three Mexico, and one Austria.\n\nOnly three foreign-born women have served as U.S. governors \u2013 [[Madeleine Kunin]] of Vermont, who was born in Switzerland; Jennifer Granholm of Michigan, who was born in Canada; and Kate Brown of Oregon, who was born in Spain.\n\n==List==\n''Governors who were succeeded by another foreign-born governor are marked with a dagger (\u2020). Governors who were preceded by another foreign-born governor are marked with a section sign (\u00a7).''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=\"70%\"\n|-\n!Name\n!State\n!Birthplace 